revMajor.name: revMajor
revMajor.description: The major number of the revision of the CIO MIB.

revMinor.name: revMinor
revMinor.description: The minor number of the revision of the CIO MIB.

devIndex.name: devIndex
devIndex.description: A unique index value for each storage device beginning with 1.

devType.name: devType
devType.description: The type of this mass storage device.

devTypeDescr.name: devTypeDescr
devTypeDescr.description: A longer description of the storage device. For example: 3.5 inch flexible diskette drives using diskettes with a maximum capacity of 1.44MB.

devSubIdentifier.name: devSubIdentifier
devSubIdentifier.description: The sub-identifier for this storage device (e.g., the device's SCSI logical unit number).

devMediaBlockSize.name: devMediaBlockSize
devMediaBlockSize.description: The size in bytes of the data blocks used on the storage media. If the media block size is unknown or inconsistent then this value shall be zero.

devFormattedMediaCapacity.name: devFormattedMediaCapacity
devFormattedMediaCapacity.description: The total size in kilobytes of this storage media after it has been formatted.

devRemovableDevice.name: devRemovableDevice
devRemovableDevice.description: If true, then this storage device is removable (e.g.: PCMCIA device).

devLoaded.name: devLoaded
devLoaded.description: If true, then the storage device is loaded.

devRemovableMedia.name: devRemovableMedia
devRemovableMedia.description: If true, then the media in this storage device is removable.

devMediaLoaded.name: devMediaLoaded
devMediaLoaded.description: If true, the media in this storage device is loaded.

devCompression.name: devCompression
devCompression.description: If true, the storage device supports compression.

devEncryption.name: devEncryption
devEncryption.description: If true, the storage device supports encryption.

ctlrIndex.name: ctlrIndex
ctlrIndex.description: A unique index value for each storage controller beginning with 1.

ctlrDescription.name: ctlrDescription
ctlrDescription.description: Name, brand, and hardware revision level of the storage controller.

ctlrProtectionManagement.name: ctlrProtectionManagement
ctlrProtectionManagement.description: Indicates whether or not the controller provides redundancy or protection against device failures.

ctlrBusMaster.name: ctlrBusMaster
ctlrBusMaster.description: If TRUE, then this storage controller is the bus master.

ctlrSecondsSinceLastPowerUp.name: ctlrSecondsSinceLastPowerUp
ctlrSecondsSinceLastPowerUp.description: The number of seconds that have passed since this controller was last powered on.

enclIndex.name: enclIndex
enclIndex.description: A unique index value for each enclosure beginning with 1.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: A unique index value for each bus port beginning with 1.

portProtocol.name: portProtocol
portProtocol.description: The protocol describing the electrical characteristics of the Bus Port. If 'Other' is used, then the Protocol Description attribute shall be used.

portProtocolDescription.name: portProtocolDescription
portProtocolDescription.description: Additional description of the protocol describe above.

portSignalCharacteristics.name: portSignalCharacteristics
portSignalCharacteristics.description: The electrical characteristics of the Bus Port being described.

portAddressDescriptor.name: portAddressDescriptor
portAddressDescriptor.description: The address descriptor for this bus port. For example the PCI slot and ID.

portIsochronous.name: portIsochronous
portIsochronous.description: Indicates whether or not the bus port supports isochronous transfers.

portMaximumWidth.name: portMaximumWidth
portMaximumWidth.description: The maximum width, in bits, of this Bus Port's data path. A value of 1 should be used for serial.

portMaximumTransferRate.name: portMaximumTransferRate
portMaximumTransferRate.description: The theoretical maximum transfer rate, in millions of bytes per second, that this Bus Port is capable of achieving under ideal conditions. A value of zero should be used if the transfer rate is less than 1 million bytes per second.

portMaximumAttachments.name: portMaximumAttachments
portMaximumAttachments.description: The maximum number of directly addressable entities supported by this bus port's protocol.

portConnectorType.name: portConnectorType
portConnectorType.description: Describes how options (cards, devices, etc.) physically connect to this port bus. If 'Other' is used, then the connector type description attribute shall be used.

portConnectorTypeDescription.name: portConnectorTypeDescription
portConnectorTypeDescription.description: Additional description of the connector described above.

portConnectorGender.name: portConnectorGender
portConnectorGender.description: Indicates the gender of the connector described above.

aggregatePExtentTable.name: aggregatePExtentTable
aggregatePExtentTable.description: A list of aggregate physical extent entries.

aggPExtentIndex.name: aggPExtentIndex
aggPExtentIndex.description: A unique index value for each aggregate physical extent beginning with 1.

aggPExtentBlocks.name: aggPExtentBlocks
aggPExtentBlocks.description: The total number of consecutive blocks (including check data blocks) contained in the aggregate p extent. The block size is determined by the storage device associated with this aggregate p extent. Note: If no redundancy group is associated with an aggregate p extent, then this number indicates that the p extent is available.

aggPExtentCheckDataBlocks.name: aggPExtentCheckDataBlocks
aggPExtentCheckDataBlocks.description: The number of blocks contained in the aggregate p extent to be used as check data. If the aggregate p extent is available, then this value shall be zero.

aggregatePsExtentTable.name: aggregatePsExtentTable
aggregatePsExtentTable.description: A list of aggregate protected space extents.

aggPsExtentIndex.name: aggPsExtentIndex
aggPsExtentIndex.description: A unique index value for each aggregate ps extent beginning with 1.

aggPsExtentBlocks.name: aggPsExtentBlocks
aggPsExtentBlocks.description: The total number of user data blocks that is both located on a single storage device and part or all of a single volume set. The block size is determined by the storage device associated with this aggregate protected space extent. Note: if no volume set is associated with an aggregate protected space extent, then this number indicates the number of blocks that are available.

volIndex.name: volIndex
volIndex.description: A unique index value for each volume set beginning with 1.

volName.name: volName
volName.description: The name of the volume set.

volCapacity.name: volCapacity
volCapacity.description: The total size in Kbytes of the user data space of this volume set.

volPSExtentStripeLength.name: volPSExtentStripeLength
volPSExtentStripeLength.description: The number of ps_extents which form a user data stripe. This value shall be zero except when the ps_extent group is used.

volPSExtentInterleaveDepth.name: volPSExtentInterleaveDepth
volPSExtentInterleaveDepth.description: The number of ps_extents to stripe as a collective set. This value shall be zero except when the ps_extent group is used.

redundancyIndex.name: redundancyIndex
redundancyIndex.description: A unique index value for each redundancy group beginning with 1.

redundancyType.name: redundancyType
redundancyType.description: This field specifies the type of redundancy formed.

worldWideIdIndex.name: worldWideIdIndex
worldWideIdIndex.description: A unique index value for each WorldWideID beginning with 1.

worldWideIdType.name: worldWideIdType
worldWideIdType.description: The type of identifier displayed by the Worldwide Identifier attribute.

worldWideId.name: worldWideId
worldWideId.description: The Worldwide Identifier for this entity.

associationIndex.name: associationIndex
associationIndex.description: A unique index value for each association beginning with 1.

associationType.name: associationType
associationType.description: This field specifies the type of the association. It contains one of the following values: 'Physical Organization', 'Logical Organization', 'Logical to Physical Organization', 'Redundancy Organization', 'Spare Organization', 'Cache', 'FRU', 'Operational State', 'Statistical', 'SubComponent Software', or 'Worldwide Identifier'.

associationObject1.name: associationObject1
associationObject1.description: The authoritative identifier for the first object referenced.

associationObject2.name: associationObject2
associationObject2.description: The authoritative identifier for the second object referenced.

busPortAssociationTable.name: busPortAssociationTable
busPortAssociationTable.description: A list of bus port associations.

busPortAssociationIndex.name: busPortAssociationIndex
busPortAssociationIndex.description: An unique index for each bus port association. This index matches an index in the association table for which bus port association information is available.

busPortAssociationNegotiatedSpeed.name: busPortAssociationNegotiatedSpeed
busPortAssociationNegotiatedSpeed.description: The maximum burst transfer rate, in millions of bytes, which was negotiated between the two associated bus ports.

busPortAssociationNegotiatedWidth.name: busPortAssociationNegotiatedWidth
busPortAssociationNegotiatedWidth.description: The width, in bits, of the bus ports' data path which was negotiated between the two associated bus ports.

componentSpareAssociationTable.name: componentSpareAssociationTable
componentSpareAssociationTable.description: A list of component spare associations.

componentSpareAssociationIndex.name: componentSpareAssociationIndex
componentSpareAssociationIndex.description: An unique index for each component spare association. This index matches an index in the association table for which component spare association information is available.

componentSpareFunctioningState.name: componentSpareFunctioningState
componentSpareFunctioningState.description: The functioning state of the spares.

overallStatus.name: overallStatus
overallStatus.description: The overall status of objects in the CIO MIB. Will be set to the worst status of any individual object.

operationalStateTable.name: operationalStateTable
operationalStateTable.description: A list of operational state information.

operationalStateIndex.name: operationalStateIndex
operationalStateIndex.description: A unique index value for each operational state table entry beginning with 1.

operationalDeviceGroupIndex.name: operationalDeviceGroupIndex
operationalDeviceGroupIndex.description: This field present for DMI compatibility - unused in SNMP, always 0.

operationalStatus.name: operationalStatus
operationalStatus.description: The operational status of the object.

operationalUsageState.name: operationalUsageState
operationalUsageState.description: The usage state of the object.

operationalAdministrativeStatus.name: operationalAdministrativeStatus
operationalAdministrativeStatus.description: The administrative state of the object.

operationalFatalErrorCount.name: operationalFatalErrorCount
operationalFatalErrorCount.description: The accumulated Fatal or Non-recoverable error count for the object.

operationalMajorErrorCount.name: operationalMajorErrorCount
operationalMajorErrorCount.description: The accumulated Major or Critical error count for the object.

operationalWarningErrorCount.name: operationalWarningErrorCount
operationalWarningErrorCount.description: The accumulated Warning or Non-critical error count for the object.

operationalCurrentErrorStatus.name: operationalCurrentErrorStatus
operationalCurrentErrorStatus.description: This attribute presents the current error status for the object. The most critical error status in effect should be presented. I.e. if a part of the object is 'Critical', while other status is 'Non-critical' then the status 'Critical' should be reported.

operationalPredictedFailureStatus.name: operationalPredictedFailureStatus
operationalPredictedFailureStatus.description: Enumeration describing the current Device Predicted Failure Status (e.g.: the S.M.A.R.T. status of the object).

statisticsIndex.name: statisticsIndex
statisticsIndex.description: A unique index value for each statistics table entry beginning with 1.

statisticsBlocksRead.name: statisticsBlocksRead
statisticsBlocksRead.description: The number of 512 byte blocks read from the object.

statisticsBlocksWritten.name: statisticsBlocksWritten
statisticsBlocksWritten.description: The number of 512 byte blocks written to the object.

statisticsReadCommands.name: statisticsReadCommands
statisticsReadCommands.description: The number of read commands issued for the object.

statisticsWriteCommands.name: statisticsWriteCommands
statisticsWriteCommands.description: The number of write commands issued for the object.

statisticsWriteBucket1.description: The number of write commands issued, 512 bytes <= size < 1K bytes.

statisticsWriteBucket2.description: The number of write commands issued, 1K bytes <= size < 2K bytes.

statisticsWriteBucket3.description: The number of write commands issued, 2K bytes <= size < 4K bytes.

trapLogNumEntries.name: trapLogNumEntries
trapLogNumEntries.description: The number entries in the Trap Log.

trapLogTable.name: trapLogTable
trapLogTable.description: A circular list of trap log entries. The number of entries is given by the value of trapLogCount. Current maximum trap log count is fixed at 125, but should be programmable (via MIB variable and .INI file) in the future.

trapLogIndex.name: trapLogIndex
trapLogIndex.description: A unique index value for each trap log table entry beginning with 1.

trapLogString.name: trapLogString
trapLogString.description: A textual string containing the text of the last trap.

trapLogTimeStamp.name: trapLogTimeStamp
trapLogTimeStamp.description: The number of seconds which have elapsed between powerup and the trap occurrence.

cycObject.name: cycObject
cycObject.description: The object identifier of the object referred to by the trap.

cycPhysicalObjectState.description: New state for the object referred to by the trap.

cycVolumeSetState.description: New state for the object referred to by the trap.

cycVolumeSetActivity.description: New activity for the object referred to by the trap.

cycVolumeSetActivityState.description: Status of a new activity for the object referred to by the trap.

cycSpareState.name: cycSpareState

cycEnclosureComponentNumber.description: The ordinal number of the part of the enclosure affected by this trap. Numbers ordinarily start at 1, such as Fan 1. A number of 0 refers to all such parts as a single piece. For example, Fan 0 refers to all fans.

cycEnclosureComponentState.name: cycEnclosureComponentState
